Physical description refers to the appearance or features of a given chemical compound including color, odor, state, taste and more in general

StringWithMarkup.String: Mustard gas is a clear amber colored oily liquid with a faint odor of mustard/garlic. It is not readily combustible. Its vapors are heavier than air, are very toxic, and can be absorbed through the skin. The effects from exposure to the material include blindness which may be delayed. Prolonged exposure of the container to fire or intense heat may cause it to violently rupture and rocket. Mustard gas is also known as dichlorodiethyl sulfide.
COLOURLESS-TO-YELLOW OILY LIQUID OR CRYSTALS WITH CHARACTERISTIC ODOUR.
Clear amber-colored oily liquid, with a faint odor of mustard/garlic.
